character_name: James Bond: An MI6 agent assigned to retrieve two stolen nuclear weapons
Domino (voice dubbed by Nikki van der Zyl):[11] Dominique "Domino" Derval is Largo's mistress. In early drafts of the screenplay
Emilio Largo (voice dubbed by Robert Rietty):[13] SPECTRE's Number Two
Fiona Volpe: SPECTRE assassin who becomes Francois Derval's mistress to kill and replace him with his double and later helps with Largo's plot in Nassau.
Felix Leiter: CIA agent who helps Bond
Count Lippe: the SPECTRE agent (ranked Number Four) in charge of the operation of replacing Derval with Angelo.
Paula Caplan: Bond's CIA ally in Nassau
the Home Secretary: British Minister who briefs the "00" agents for Operation Thunderball and has doubts about Bond's efficiency
Pinder: Bahaman intelligence operative who serves as Bond and Leiter's contact in Nassau.
François Derval / Angelo Palazzi (credited for Palazzi): François Derval is a French Air Force pilot assigned to the NATO staff and also Domino's brother. He is killed by Angelo
Vargas: Largo's personal assistant and primary henchman.
Ernst Stavro Blofeld (voiced by Eric Pohlmann): The head of SPECTRE
